<paragraph id="8BDF3692712BFFF5D9D10D74FB78071C" blockId="2.[166,1225,538,675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
<keyLead id="309195A7712BFFF5D9D10D74FB78071C" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
1 Face and mesoscutum granulate (
<figureCitation id="135B2A17712BFFF5DB4A0D74FDC00760" box="[573,625,538,560]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1792,1814]" captionTargetBox="[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-218@2.[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Allomacrus spp.: 1–2 — A. arcticus; 3–4 — A. longecaudatus; 1, 4 — habitus (lateral view); 2–3 — face (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377905/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Fore wing with vein 3rs-m usually present. Hind coxa and femur fuscous (
<figureCitation id="135B2A17712BFFF5D8F00D59FE08071D" box="[391,441,567,589]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1792,1814]" captionTargetBox="[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-218@2.[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Allomacrus spp.: 1–2 — A. arcticus; 3–4 — A. longecaudatus; 1, 4 — habitus (lateral view); 2–3 — face (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377905/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">fig. 4</figureCitation>
). ............................................................................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D11712BFFF5DD510D59FB78071C" baseAuthorityName="Strobl" baseAuthorityYear="1903" box="[1062,1225,567,588]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Allomacrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longecaudatus">
<emphasis id="B914EA80712BFFF5DD510D59FB78071C" box="[1062,1225,567,588]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">A. longecaudatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712BFFF5D9D10D3AFB78073A" blockId="2.[166,1225,538,675]" box="[166,1225,596,618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
<keyLead id="309195A7712BFFF5D9D10D3AFB78073A" box="[166,1225,596,618]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
– Face and mesoscutum smooth (
<figureCitation id="135B2A17712BFFF5DB550D3AFDE5073A" box="[546,596,596,618]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1792,1814]" captionTargetBox="[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-218@2.[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Allomacrus spp.: 1–2 — A. arcticus; 3–4 — A. longecaudatus; 1, 4 — habitus (lateral view); 2–3 — face (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377905/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Fore wing with vein 3rs-m absent. ............................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30942E37712BFFF5D9D10D1FFB7807F3" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712BFFF5D9D10D1FFB7907D6" blockId="2.[166,1225,538,675]" box="[166,1224,625,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
<keyLead id="309195A7712BFFF5D9D10D1FFB7907D6" box="[166,1224,625,647]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
2 Ovipositor at most weakly longer than the hind tibia length. Hind femur fuscous. ................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C604D11712BFFF5DD1D0D1FFB7907D6" authorityName="Humala" authorityYear="2002" box="[1130,1224,625,646]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Allomacrus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="487" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subtilis">
<emphasis id="B914EA80712BFFF5DD1D0D1FFB7907D6" box="[1130,1224,625,646]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">A. subtilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDF3692712BFFF5D9D10DE3FB7807F3" blockId="2.[166,1225,538,675]" box="[166,1225,653,675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
<keyLead id="309195A7712BFFF5D9D10DE3FB7807F3" box="[166,1225,653,675]" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">
– Ovipositor at least 1.8 times as long as the hind tibia length. Hind femur orange (
<figureCitation id="135B2A17712BFFF5DA8E0DE3FB9807F3" box="[1017,1065,653,675]" captionStart="Figs 1–4" captionStartId="2.[166,205,1792,1814]" captionTargetBox="[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetId="figure-218@2.[263,1128,718,1776]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figs 1–4. Allomacrus spp.: 1–2 — A. arcticus; 3–4 — A. longecaudatus; 1, 4 — habitus (lateral view); 2–3 — face (frontal view)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6377905" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6377905/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="487">fig. 1</figureCitation>
). ....... 
